<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-666-738  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 666 738.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Sept 12 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Xerox translator keeps charts intact. (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McCormick, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Xerox Corp. (product introduction)Systran Machine Translation Systems Inc. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    XRX.andO;Product:   Viewpoint Machine Translation Interface (Computer program)(product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionSoftware PublishersSoftware packagesLanguage Translation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>XEROX TRANSLATOR KEEPS CHARTS INTACT MCLEAN, VIRGINIA, U.S.A., 1989 SEP 8(NB) -- Xerox Corp.'s ViewPoint Machine Translation Interface is claimed totranslate from English into German, Spanish, Italian, and Portuguese at anaccuracy rate of 95 percent, while retaining non-text charts and graphics intheir original form.andP;  The SYSTRAN translation software was developed by LaJolla, California-based SYSTRAN Machine Translation Systems Inc. and the$3,500 ViewPoint software provides an interface between Xerox 6085workstations and IBM mainframe compatible computers running the SYSTRANsoftware.andP;  This is a major improvement because previous translation softwarerequired the operator to recreate any graphics by hand.andP;  (JohnMcCormick/19890908/Press Contact: Barbara E. Burke, Xerox, 213-333-3613, orAllen Portella, Systran, 619-459-6700)</TEXT></DOC>